    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Enoggera?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Enoggera values are driven by its position as an accessible inner north-western address relative to Ashgrove and Bardon, the consistent demand from defence-affiliated families, creek and parkland amenity along Enoggera Creek, and the suburb's settled owner-occupied street character. As Ashgrove and Bardon have moved up the price ladder, buyers doing active comparisons have increasingly recognised that Enoggera offers the same fundamental lifestyle at a meaningfully lower entry point. That spillover demand has underpinned price progression in the suburb.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Enoggera?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Enoggera homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The suburb draws first home buyers, defence families, and buyers priced out of Ashgrove and Bardon who arrive with clear criteria. When a property is correctly priced and presents well, it attracts genuine inquiry from multiple profiles. Overpricing against the Ashgrove and Bardon comparables that buyers are running in parallel stalls campaigns quickly; correct pricing produces focused attention and decisive offers.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Enoggera?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Enoggera offers a family-oriented lifestyle about seven kilometres north-west of the Brisbane CBD. Enoggera Creek and the surrounding greenway provide active recreation and green space that families value, and the suburb's established streets give it a community character that residents are attached to. Ashgrove's retail and cafe precinct is close, bus access to the CBD is practical, and the inner ring road location means the city is a short commute rather than a long haul. The suburb's community feel and low-turnover residential character are part of what buyers are purchasing here.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Enoggera a good suburb for first home buyers?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Enoggera has consistently attracted first home buyers who want an inner north-western address without the price point of Ashgrove or Bardon. The suburb delivers on the practical requirements: it is inside the ring road, has established community infrastructure, creek and parkland access, bus connections to the CBD, and school options. For a first purchase that prioritises inner suburban living within a realistic budget, Enoggera represents genuine value in the north-western corridor and has the fundamentals that support long-term capital growth.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

